= Acknowledgements

This paper describes a joint effort by the three named authors. Alex Carreras Forns led the design and the bulk of the implementation across the crawler, the wiki builder, the catalog API, and the agent's tool surface. Josep Carreras Molins contributed mentorship throughout, code review across all phases, and the deployment work that brought the system from a local prototype to the running public instance. Claude Code provided pair-programming support across every phase of the project, from the initial site exploration through the Terraform infrastructure module to the scope guardrails and the typesetting of this manuscript.

This work is submitted in support of the first author's application to La Salle Campus Barcelona's Bachelor in Artificial Intelligence and Data Science (programme id `en/bachelor-artificial-intelligence-and-data-science`). The choice of corpus is therefore not accidental: the system retrieves and answers questions about the programme its first author is applying to, and the application reads its own catalog. We hope the paper makes the engineering judgements behind that choice visible enough to be evaluated on technical merit.

We thank the maintainers of the open-source dependencies the work rests on: Agno for the streaming agent framework that made the SSE adapter tractable, FastAPI and Starlette for the server, Model2Vec for the static-embedding implementation that keeps the semantic pole lightweight, Typst and Fletcher for the typesetting and diagram libraries used to produce this manuscript, Caddy for the TLS edge, and Terraform for reproducible infrastructure. We also acknowledge the OpenAI Responses API for the `gpt-5.4` model that drives the streaming agent.
